# chat

Interactive terminal REPL front-end â€” the Claude-CLI-style daily driver.
Additive: reuses `run_single` / the tool surface / the prompt registry
unchanged. The deterministic benchmark path (`luxe maintain`, `benchmarks/`)
never touches this module.

## Must
- Every user turn drives exactly ONE `run_single()` call; conversation state
  lives in `ChatSession`, folded into `goal=` + a tagged `extra_context` block â€”
  never by forking `run_agent`'s message loop or changing its signature
- Context precedence (highest wins): current user turn > project memory >
  conversation summary. `extra_context` is tagged `<project_memory>` /
  `<conversation_history>` / `<current_request>` so history can't read as commands
- Default slot config = champion in chat/plan/code (`model_for_slot` returns the
  monolith model when `slots` is None or `model_key=""`); byte-identical model
  selection to `single_64gb.yaml`
- Multi-slot fan-out activates ONLY on explicit `configs/chat.yaml` `slots:` â€”
  the sanctioned, opt-in exception to luxe.sdd "no per-task model selection",
  scoped to this front-end
- Slot routing is visible: the render footer shows the fired slot + model every
  turn; `/use <slot>` and `/model <slot> <id>` are explicit user overrides
- The `chat` slot (the catch-all `review` inference routes to for greetings,
  small talk, and general Q&A) uses the CONVERSATIONAL persona: `prepare_turn`
  swaps the role's `system_prompt_id`/`task_prompt_id` to the registry variant
  `chat_conversational` so it answers directly instead of running the code-
  maintenance orientation loop (a bare "hello" used to `list_dir` + read the
  README + emit a "final report"). The focused `code`/`plan` slots keep the
  baseline maintenance/planning prompts, and the swap is SKIPPED for `/plan`
  drafting (`plan_mode`) and autonomous `/goal` rounds (`session.goal_active`) â€”
  those are genuine task turns even when `continue work` routes to `chat`. Model
  selection is unchanged (still champion); the string lives in the prompt
  registry (never inline in this module)
- Different-model slot use sequences weight swaps via
  `Backend.unload_all_loaded` + `thermal_guard`; swap count + seconds are
  instrumented and surfaced; keep chat-slot model resident, group code work
- The history summarizer (`chat/summarize.py`) is NON-model, deterministic, and
  versioned (`SUMMARIZER_VERSION`); its output is persisted to `fold.jsonl`
- Cancel during a turn cancels MID-GENERATION: the CancelToken is set (the line
  REPL via a SIGINT handler; the TUI via the `escape`/`ctrl+c` key binding) and
  the streaming `on_token` callback (chat-only, `stream=True`) raises
  `ChatCancelled` (a KeyboardInterrupt, so loop.py's `except Exception` can't
  swallow it) at the next token â€” not only at tool boundaries. Persists the
  partial transcript and returns to the prompt (no process exit). In the TUI,
  cancel ALSO dismisses any open `PromptScreen` modal so a blocked worker
  unwinds. Responsiveness is bounded by the backend's token-streaming cadence; an
  in-flight `bash` subprocess finishes first. The benchmark/maintain path
  (`on_token=None`, `stream=False`) is unaffected and keeps tool-boundary
  cancellation.
- The per-turn pipeline is UI-agnostic: `prepare_turn` (slot/role/tool/ledger
  setup + the verbatim `run_single` closure) and `finalize_turn` (persistence +
  `TurnOutcome`) are shared by BOTH front-ends; `run_single`'s call args are
  assembled identically so the benchmark path stays byte-identical. Interactive
  sub-prompts (/plan choice, gitkit clone URL, compare vote) go through one
  `reader`/`prompt_user` seam â€” `console.input` on the line path, a modal on the
  TUI. `_run_plan`/`_run_goal_loop` take injectable `run_turn`/`reader` so the
  supervisor logic is single-sourced.
- Working-state ledger (`state/ledger.py`, persisted to
  `~/.luxe/sessions/<id>/ledger.json`): a compact
  decided/completed/in_progress/blocked/files record injected as a high-precedence
  `<working_state>` block by `build_extra_context` so `continue work`/`/goal`
  rounds consult known state instead of re-reading plan.md + all sources. Two
  feeds: deterministic (write/edit paths observed from the tool-event stream) and
  model-driven (the always-exposed `update_ledger` tool, wired via run_single's
  extra-tool seam). Empty ledger â†’ byte-identical legacy context (no block)
- `/verbose [diff|full|off]` controls tool-IO visibility and `/reasoning` toggles
  live streaming of model prose â€” INDEPENDENT session flags (reasoning is often
  low-signal; never coupled). Verbose reuses the `on_tool_event` seam
  (`format_tool_call_verbose`): `diff` renders edit_file as a unified diff +
  write_file headers + capped result bodies + the ledger view; `full` dumps whole
  files. All content is Rich-escaped and bounded. Reasoning rides the same
  streaming `on_token` seam as Ctrl-C, line-buffered so it scrolls above the Live
  region. Both default off â†’ unchanged one-line summaries
- `/goal <objective>` is an autonomous supervisor in the REPL loop: round 1 sends
  the objective, later rounds send `continue work`, each printing `[goal round
  N/M]`. Termination keys on OBSERVABLE state (iteration-5, C1/D1/D6): a "settled"
  round (files_changed==0) is DONE when it shows GREEN tests (parsed from tool
  output by `parse_test_result` â€” passed>0, zero failed/errors) OR carries
  `LUXE_GOAL_DONE` + a grown ledger `completed`, for 2 consecutive rounds. The
  green-tests path completes a finished run even if the model never logged
  `completed` or signaled (the iter-5 run-2/3 false-STUCK); the sentinel path alone
  never suffices (keeps the 32K false-done shut). It does NOT require `in_progress`
  empty. STUCK has two guards: idle (settled rounds, no new completed, â‰Ą3) and
  THRASH (rounds that ran tests without reducing failures and added no completed,
  â‰Ą3 â€” catches the editâ†’testâ†’same-failures loop; no-test rounds don't count, so
  staged work isn't punished). Completion is checked first and resets both. The
  STUCK message reports observable state (files built + last test result), never
  "completed=0 â€¦ likely NOT done". Crash resilience retries on CONSECUTIVE failures;
  a tool-fingerprint guard is a faster stuck trip; a â‰¤32K window prints a
  low-context advisory. The pure `evaluate_goal_round()` + `parse_test_result()`
  are unit-tested. Requires write mode;
  Ctrl-C or `/goal stop` halts it
- `/plan <objective>` drafts a plan in a forced READ-ONLY turn (PLAN_HINT, reusing
  make_read_only_role) then prompts save / execute / both / discard. Save never
  clobbers an existing `plan.md` (writes `.luxe/plans/<id>-<n>.md`); execute seeds
  the `/goal` runner and injects the drafted plan as a `<plan>` provenance block
  so the agent keeps following it
- `/terse` (default ON) injects the registry `TERSE_HINT` `<response_style>` block
  to cut model prose ("report only deltas") â€” carved out so it never abbreviates
  tool output, errors, or skips needed reads/confirmations. `/debug` is a
  convenience that flips `/verbose full` + `/reasoning` together. `/verbose` now
  renders code via rich `Syntax` and edits as highlighted diffs, with a crash-safe
  plain-text fallback
- The chat palette tracks the user's theme: tool lines, status bar, ledger,
  banner, and prompt arrows resolve colors from `theme.role_styles()` roles
  (`accent`/`success`/`error`/`warn`/`slot`/`diff_*`/â€¦) instead of hardcoded hex â€”
  ANSI-named fallbacks track the terminal profile, and the `slot` segment no
  longer hardcodes magenta. `auto` (default) tracks the YASL/terminal theme;
  `--theme cool|warm|mono` (C-T) selects a curated luxe palette (256/RGB) that
  overrides terminal ANSI â€” needed because a standard-index YASL theme equals the
  ANSI fallback, so auto looks unchanged
- Goal completion is SENTINEL-required + ledger-corroborated (C1): a settled round
  is done only when `completed` is non-empty, grew at least once this run, and the
  reply carries `LUXE_GOAL_DONE` â€” for 2 consecutive rounds. It does NOT require
  `in_progress` empty (models leave stale plan-phase headers â†’ the iter-4 a5812
  false-STUCK). Completion is checked before stuck and resets the stuck counter;
  `in_progress` pruning/clearing is cosmetic provenance, never control flow. The
  per-round decision is the pure `evaluate_goal_round()` (unit-tested)
- Context % is one metric end-to-end (C2): `AgentResult.final_context_pressure`
  (last per-step instantaneous, via the chat-only `on_progress` callback) drives
  both the live and between-turn status bar, matching the `[token-progress]` line;
  the footer shows `ctx(peak)` separately. `huge` (256K) is the new `/ctx` ceiling,
  clamped by `num_ctx_max`; the startup banner shows the git build via
  `buildinfo.version_string()`, and `luxe chat` gains
  `--verbose/--show-reasoning/--no-terse/--debug/--theme` startup flags
- Static analyzers (`tools/analysis.py`) resolve via PATH â†’ `python -m <module>`
  â†’ `uvx` (NO auto-install â€” agent venvs may be frozen) and degrade to a
  SUCCESSFUL machine-readable `{"status":"skipped",â€¦}` when unavailable, so a
  missing linter is never misread as a pass. The `[analyzers]` extra pins the
  toolchain (ruff/mypy/bandit/pip-audit)
- Write tools default OFF (read-only, reusing the `serve`/`make_read_only_role`
  precedent); `/write` toggles; write-mode is shown in the footer every turn
- In read-only mode a lowest-precedence `<session_mode>` block (string =
  `prompts.READ_ONLY_CHAT_HINT`, never inlined here) is injected so the model
  points the user at `/write` instead of claiming luxe can't create/edit files
- `/ctx <tier>` sets a per-session `num_ctx` override (small/medium/large/xlarge);
  it is CHAT-ONLY and always clamped to the role's `num_ctx_max` (config) so a
  request can never exceed what the box/model holds. `num_ctx_max: 0` (default)
  forbids any expansion. Resize is never silent â€” high context pressure only
  *suggests* the next tier; the user opts in. The benchmark/maintain path never
  reads `num_ctx_max` and is unaffected.
- `/bash` toggles unrestricted shell (default OFF = hardened allowlist). When ON
  AND write mode is on, the turn passes `unrestricted_bash_def()` +
  `make_bash_fn(unrestricted=True)` through `run_single`'s extra-tool seam,
  overriding the allowlisted bash for that run only. Effective only in write mode
  (bash is stripped in read-only). Visible on the slot line every turn. The
  benchmark/maintain path passes no extra tools, so its bash stays allowlisted.
- `luxe chat --dev` starts with write + unrestricted bash ON (sticky equivalent
  of `/write` + `/bash`), so dev work doesn't re-toggle each session
- Defaults stay safe (read-only + allowlisted bash) but the state must be VISIBLE
  and flag-gated failures must be SELF-EXPLAINING: write mode (non-dev) injects
  `restricted_bash_def()` + `make_bash_fn(restricted_hint=True)` so an
  allowlist/chain/substitution rejection front-loads "enable unrestricted dev mode
  with /bash" onto the error (survives the 80-char tool-line truncation) and the
  def tells the model to surface the flag rather than retry. Genuine errors
  (mismatched quotes, timeouts, non-zero exit) are NOT augmented. The startup
  banner names the initial mode + toggles; the status-bar chips show live state.
- The status bar (`chat/status.py`) order (user spec):
  `path Â· git Â· ctx Â· cache Â· start Â· last Â· write Â· bash Â· slot Â· model`.
  `ctx` = `ctx N% <window-size>` (size in the K/M context convention, e.g. 128K;
  the size shows immediately â€” seeded from the slot's role num_ctx at startup â€”
  and the % appears once a turn measures usage);
  `cache` = resident prompt size (luxe has no cross-turn prompt cache â€” each turn
  is a fresh `run_single`, so it's the prompt/KV size processed last turn, NOT an
  Anthropic-style cache); `write`/`bash` show explicit on/off; the luxe mode
  (slot, e.g. `chat`) is its own segment, then the model name pinned last. The
  startup banner is intentionally minimal (session + /help) â€” repo/slot/model/mode
  are NOT reprinted there since the bar already shows them. `fields()` (â†’ `list[Segment]`, each
  with a drop-`priority`) is the single source of order/content; `toolbar()`
  (prompt_toolkit bottom bar â€” its grey/reversed background is overridden to
  `bg:default` so the bar sits on the terminal background), `status_markup()`
  (plain-input fallback), and `to_rich_text()`/`LiveActivity` (in-turn live bar)
  all render from it so they never drift. `fit(segs, width)` is responsive: it
  drops low-value segments (cache=8, start/last=7) highest-first, then
  middle-ellipsises the elastic path; path/git/ctx/model (priority 1â€“2) protected.
  Git state is TTL-cached to avoid per-keystroke `git` spawns.
- Colours follow the user's ACTIVE Claude statusline theme, resolved LIVE by
  `chat/theme.py`: read the theme name (`CLAUDE_STATUSLINE_THEME` env â†’
  `~/.claude/statusline-theme` â†’ `claude-dark`), import the user's
  yet-another-statusline `themes` module via the `~/.claude/statusline_command.py`
  symlink, and convert each role's ANSI escape to a (ptk, Rich) pair â€” ANSI 0-15
  â†’ NAMED colours (track the iTerm2 profile), 16-255 â†’ fixed xterm value,
  rgb/default pass through. The GIT segment is styled by theme ROLE
  (branch/commit/dirty/safe/warn/alert), cached per process; the rest use a
  sparing luxe palette per the user's spec: path BLUE (fixed hex â€” the terminal's
  ANSI-blue slot renders orange on the user's profile), luxe-mode/slot PURPLE,
  model name YELLOW, state on=GREEN/off=RED, `ctx`/`write`/`bash` LABEL words in
  terminal default fg ("white"/prominent â€” true white would vanish on the light
  bg), other labels + separators grey, values = default fg. Falls back to a
  built-in llmtop-equivalent ANSI map if the
  repo/symlink/import is absent. NOTE: this reads only the theme-name file and imports the user's pure
  themes module for COLOURS â€” it is NOT the memory subsystem and injects no
  `~/.claude` content into context (the luxe.sdd/chat.sdd `~/.claude` prohibition
  is scoped to context/memory, not UI theming).
- The interactive front-end is a full-screen **Textual** app (`chat/tui.py`,
  `tui.css`). Layout (topâ†’bottom):

      â”Ś RichLog#transcript â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ (1fr, scrollable; banner, hint, turns,
      â”‚                                  tool lines, final answers)
      â”ś Static#generating â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ (transient; spinner Â· elapsed Â· tool
      â”‚                                  counts Â· streamed preview â€” turn only)
      â”ś StatusBar#status â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ (status.fields()/fit()/to_rich_text())
      â”” Input#prompt â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ (docked at the very bottom)

  The blocking turn runs on a Textual thread worker (`@work(thread=True,
  exclusive=True)` â€” exclusive + disabling the Input enforces ONE run_single per
  turn). Tool events marshal to the UI thread via `call_from_thread`; tokens
  COALESCE on the worker into a rolling buffer that a UI-thread `set_interval`
  timer (~10 Hz) renders into `#generating` (never per-token `call_from_thread` â€”
  flood/deadlock). A final frame flushes on completion. The final answer renders
  via `build_final_renderable` into the RichLog. Cancel = key binding (see the
  cancel Must). Front-end selection / fallback:

  | condition                                  | front-end          |
  |--------------------------------------------|--------------------|
  | stdout is a TTY AND `textual` installed AND not `--resume` | Textual TUI |
  | otherwise (CI, pipes, textual-absent, resume) | line REPL (`repl.py`) |

  The line REPL keeps its prior behaviour: a `rich.Live` 3-line `LiveActivity`
  (preview Â· activity Â· status) when `console.is_terminal`, else `Status` + line
  streaming. Both feed off the chat-only `on_token` seam (`stream=True`); the
  benchmark/maintain path (`on_token=None`, `stream=False`) is untouched.

## Must not
- Modify `agents/loop.py`'s `backend.chat` call site or `run_agent` signature
  (preserves benchmark determinism)
- Introduce any system/task prompt strings here â€” those stay in
  `agents/prompts.py`. `extra_context` is runtime conversation framing, not a
  registry prompt
- Auto-open PRs from a chat turn (the PR cycle stays in `luxe maintain`/`luxe pr`)
- Let `configs/chat.yaml` change the behavior of `single_64gb.yaml` / maintain

## Owns
- src/luxe/chat/**
